I did it fully awake and the surgeon was super cool and was easy to talk to, I actually had a little fun just talking to everyone and learning about the process. My son went through a little over 2 yrs. of starting & finishing orthodontics at this office.
His experience was great. Staff was helpful & comforting during his treatment.
Now his braces are off and we are so pleased.

Now my daughter is starting her treatment of braces. She was very concerned, but rest assured after her first visit.
We've seen both the Dentist and the Orthodontist here. I've been very satisfied.
I have more to say about the Orthodontist only because we saw much more of him. He is very thorough and made us feel comfortable with each visit. He took just the right amount of time with each and every one of his patients that I observed, showing he IS dedicated.

The receptionists in the front behind the desk, are Always pleasant and have a smile to welcome you.
The ladies are ready to set up your next appointment when your finished and ready to leave.

Paulina (receptionist) is such an asset. She seems to love her position here and has such positive energy each and Everytime we've come in. I Really appreciate That and her.

I am grateful for our experience so far and will continue to come here.
I'm a retired orthodontic assistant myself, so I know What to look for and What stands out as far as OSHA Requirements. I've never been disappointed in what I've observed here.

The General Dentist is So happy, he also brings such a Positive, Delightful Joy in saying hello, genuinely asking how you are, caring about you as the patient and as an individual. I'm considering redoing my cosmetic veneers. I was surprised in the time & attention he gave me during my consultation. That says and shows alot about him and his connection with his patients.
Our family is very pleased with Town and Country Dental and will highly recommend them.
Yes, you'll have a wait, but that's to be expected When The Dentists/Orthodontist are Great. So get over it and say to yourself : "This Is My Time to catch up on a good book, or resond to emails".

S. Fitzpatrick< /Text>

<user_name>Z</user_name>< Review>
Craving for the most delicious dumpling in the Bay Area? This is the right place to go have it. We have been visiting this place for almost 4 years and we never get tired of coming here even though we have to commute for about 40 minutes. You will leave this place with that tasty flavor in your mouth. Service is  awesome!. It's a family style little cozy restaurant and I really love that the waitress recognizes us every time we go there which means, they take customers seriously! I love their tea, it's yummy and generous!
I would give this restaurant 10 stars if I could!!! Strongly recommend!< /Review>

<gmapID>0x808fbf4e2b7464e7:0xcff69085eac00ec0< /gmapID><review>Came in a group of 6 around 12:35PM on a Saturday.

Average prices for standard pork and cabbage dumplings are $7.55, definitely slight raise in prices since my previous visit.

Ordered their soup dumplings, pot stickers, 3 flavor (pork, shrimp, chives) dumpling, regular pork and cabbage dumplings, popcorn chicken, 3 flavor fried rice, pig ears, and walnut shrimp.

Order your appetizers early, we got the pig ears at the very end. Also note that the pig ears are the sliced string-ish form, not the thin wide slices. Also did not come with standard garlic and ginger sauce.

Overall, dumplings here are bomb. Their sambal has a great kick and works great with any dumpling. Eat the pot stickers early or they'll steam up and become soupy inside.< /review>< userid>

<UserId.>115645716690963501245</UserId.><user_name>Daniel Chen< /user_name>< Time>
1455834920967</Time>
< rate>
5< /rate>
< review>
I love coming here for a multitude of reasons. I think dumplings are probably the best foods to eat, I could probably eat them forever and King of Dumplings always satisfies my cravings. What puts them apart from House of Dumplings in nearby Union City is that they have a greater selection of Hand-Pulled noodle dishes. Their dumplings are comparable to each other, and even comparable with Kingdom of Dumplings in SF, another popular spot. I highly recommend the Pork and Napa Dumplings, Chicken and Corn Dumplings, or Lamb and Vegetable Dumplings. If you are looking for noodles then I suggest the Dumpling Noodle because it comes with 6 pieces of your choice of dumpling. The prices are very fair as well, which is what makes this restaurant my go-to...cheap, delicious, consistent, no wait..absolutely perfect.</review>

<user_id>105342026823861995943</user_id><gmap_id>0x8094681bc197405b:0xfc8e81a99ac8dd9b<//gmap_id>< review>
First let me say that P&P brews the best beer by far in Fresno. Really. But if you go, take a measuring cup, to make sure you get what you paid for. For his chosen customers he will use oversized glasses and fill them to the rim, for others he will use undersized glasses, leave half an inch of space at the top, and then lay in an excessive head of foam. Regular customers have asked why he illegally cheats some customers and gives extras to other customers, and his response is typically to tell all of them  "I don't need you, if you don't like it just leave."
The beer is great, but the owner has some questionable business practices, has a strange concept of customer service, and has little respect for his clients.
Maybe this attitude of his comes from being bankrolled by daddy and by 'working' as and when he pleases in daddy's insurance business.
Customers who feel they have been repeatedly cheated by him have talked about suing him, so maybe daddy will see fit to give him insurance to cover that eventuality.</review>

<time>1611563014110< /time>< rate>
2</rate>
< Review>
I ordered delivery, so I can't comment on Cinnaholic's customer service or atmosphere. As far as the cinnamon rolls go: I was skeptical that they'd be able to pull off piling a bunch of toppings on a cinnamon roll without it coming out sickningly sweet. Unfortunately, my skepticism was warranted. The dough was more or less taste free and under-done in the middle. The brownie chunks on the death-by-chocolate were stale, and none of the various chocolate toppings were particularly rich or chocolatey. With the cinnamon/chocolate combo, I was hoping for a flavor inspired by Mexican Hot Chocolate. I got simple syrup instead. The  Carmel Apple Pie flavor was slightly better. On one hand, the apple pieces and pecans cut the otherwise overwhelming sweetness a little, but the caramel frosting/caramel sauce combo was overkill, especially since neither flavor had any redeeming nuance.</Review>

<review>I tried this for my first time through GrubHub, and I was so pleasantly surprised by my Cinnaholic experience! I have severe food allergies to peanuts and tree nuts, and I was comfortable ordering from here because their products are nut free, with the exception of some nut toppings. I typically can never have cinnamon rolls that aren't home made because nuts are commonly used as a topping or in the cinnamon mix. I ordered a plain cinnamon roll with vanilla frosting, chocolate chips, and brownie bites, and it was absolutely delicious! Since it was dairy free, I didn't need to refrigerate it overnight, and it held up for at least 2-3 days. I also tried the cookie dough, which was also delicious. I'm hoping to order it with my colleagues again soon.</review>< Pics>

<UserId.>101741871043887400347<//UserId.><time>1506107224690< /time><Pics>None<//Pics><gmapID>0x80c2c710a4194f8d:0x1d57c63d84656650</gmapID>< Text>
This is one of those vegan places you don't need to think of as a vegan place, but just a delicious place (that happens to be vegan)!  My sister is vegan as was visiting from out of town and learned about this place from one of her favorite youtubers.

It has clear signage out front, but the free parking behind the building didn't have any signs, so that was a little confusing.  We were fine, so it's great that this has plenty of parking... I just wasn't 100% sure at the time if I was supposed to park there or not (pretty sure I was).  There are no tables inside, so that kind of stinks.  But there are a few tables outside, which we took advantage of.  There wasn't many people there so we were fine... but I do highly recommend this place get more tables.

Now for the food... you order a cinnamon bun and pick from a TON of frostings!  It was amazing how many flavors they had!  They'll let you sample them too.  Then you add your toppings and there you have it.  Everything is vegan, and tasted amazing (and I'm not a vegan).  So this is a really great place to take your vegan friends when they come in town and you want some dessert or a snack outing that's something a littler different than ice cream.</Text>

<GmapID>0x80c32f18076cfca9:0xac708300980b145c< /GmapID><user>104380250570694416583<//user>< text>
Here's the thing: to get local flavor, homemade cooking, and cheap food made with real ingredients, you sometimes have to put up with long waits and dirty floors.
La Poblanita is totally worth it. The house-made salsa has a nice kick to it, and is smooth enough to eat a whole bunch before the food arrives. The portions are manageable, which reflects to fair price.
When someone from out of town asks for good Mexican food, take them here.<//text>

4< /Rate>
< Text>
I am labeling this place purely as "okay" because I have been here one other time and was severely disappointed. My first time there I ordered in-store, waited 30 minutes for my food (boneless wings) and they just... did not seem right. They seemed undercooked? Chewy? Rubbery? Whatever it was I threw most of it away and was very unhappy... fast forward almost a year and I try them again for their .60 cent boneless wing Monday. I ordered online, got all my food cooked "well done" and came to pick it up. I showed up early so I had to wait but not nearly as long as ordering in-store. Overall, I was VERY impressed. I guess the secret is getting it all well done because my wings tasted perfectly cooked, I got plain and Garlic Parm flavor. Absolutely delicious and will be coming back. Their fries are good too! Cajun seasoning, I think. Only downside is they charge 1.09 for a dipping sauce.</Text>

< text>
El Torito used to be my favorite place to dine out with family and friends, but now it seems that the taste of the food as gone left. When I think of Mexican food I think of a dish that is well seasoned with plenty of flavor, and El Torito was that place for me. I don't know if the cooks are not that experienced with the food items, or if it's just a lack of care when preparing these dishes. But when you think of paying $23 dollars for a meal on more than one occasion and the taste of the food is bland, not only do you feel let down, but money has been wasted. I do hope that in the future El Torito do better so that they can once again be my favorite place to dine out. Until then, I will have to look further, and most likely will not return back to this restaurant.< /text>

<name>Rodney S< /name><review>BIRTHDAY MONTH=BIRTHDAY COUPONS=HAPPY RODNEY

Free entr√©e (up to $12.99)

Having been to the other nearby El Torito locations at the Long Beach Towne Centre (now closed) and in La Palma, I decided to visit the Lakewood location to redeem my free entr√©e coupon for their lunch buffet.

Checking out the spread, I immediately noticed El Torito's lunch buffet had received an upgrade since last time I dined on their buffet.  New options of meat, ceviche & even dessert welcomed me as I filled plate after plate.

After polishing off a heaping mound of plates, I found I enjoyed what El Torito now has to offer with their lunch buffet.  My favorites were the spicy soup (whose name escapes me) and the chocolate chip cookie brownies.

Besides the lunch buffet, El Torito has many daily specials, including Happy Hour & AYCE Taco Tuesday.

Service was good.  The attendant was quick to refill my soda water & he automatically redeemed the birthday coupon for me when I received the bill.  Plenty of seating around the restaurant.  I sat at the cantina, where I could easily access the buffet.

Parking is via a private lot.  El Torito is on the corner of Lakewood & Candlewood, outside of the Lakewood Center.

No complaints here!  El Torito is one of the good ol' reliables when my birthday month comes around.  The newly revamped buffet offers a varied selection of items to consume, which would appease all types of folks, from vegan to carnivore.  Service has been equally on par, from my experience thus far.  I've been satisfied during every visit and wouldn't mind coming back again.

Highly recommend!
NOMNOMNOMNOMNOMNOMNOMNOM< /review>< gmap_id>
